OL,6,FAlan Witney-Price, the boss of Sark
OL,7,FElectricity Limited, believes a
OL,8,Fdecision has been made behind
OL,9,Fresidents' backs and says he has been
OL,10,Ftrying to spend millions on upgrading
OL,11,Fthe ageing electricity network for
OL,12,Fyears.
OL,14,FHe explains: "I have no desire to sell
OL,15,Fto Chief Pleas. I have concerns in
OL,16,Fterms of how they will run it, it's
OL,17,Fpersonality rather than policy, and
OL,18,Fthat's a problem for me.
