OL,4,Cif loan agreed for utility buyout
OL,6,F"Guernsey does not have a formal
OL,7,Fconstitutional responsibility in
OL,8,Frelation to these matters, but it
OL,9,Fmight be considered that the situation
OL,10,Fhas reached a point where there is a
OL,11,Fmoral argument for the States of
OL,12,FGuernsey to support Chief Pleas, by
OL,13,Fway of a financial loan, to secure
OL,14,Freliable and sustainable provision for
OL,15,Fenergy generation and supply in Sark."
OL,17,FMr Witney-Price claims that "most
OL,18,FConseillors didn't even know that
OL,19,Fthese backroom deals had been done".
